frontmatter.name: swFileLoadWarning_e
frontmatter.description: File load warnings for ISldWorks::OpenDoc6. Bitmask.

title: swFileLoadWarning_e
description: File load warnings for ISldWorks::OpenDoc6. Bitmask.

values.description: or 0x80 = Warning appears because the document is already open.
or 0x40000 = Warning appears that non-critical data in the document was automatically repaired.
or 0x40 = Warning appears because the document was defined in the context of another existing document that is not loaded.
or 0x8000 = Warning appears if document is opened silently and swOpenDocOptions_AutoMissingConfig is specified.
or 0x80000 = Warning appears that critical data in the document was automatically repaired.
or 0x4000 = Warning appears because some dimensions are referenced to the models incorrectly; these dimensions are highlighted in red in the drawing.
or 0x8 = Warning appears because radial dimension arrows now displayed outside when the dimension text is outside of the arc or circle.
or 0x800Warning appears asking the user if he or she wants to convert this drawing's surface finish symbols to the sizes specified in ANSI Y14.36M-1996 and ISO 1302-1978.
or 0x100 = Warning appears because the only RapidDraft format conversion that can take place is a drawing document that is not Detached.
or 0x1 = Warning appears if the internal ID of the document does not match the internal ID saved with the referencing document.

or 0x10000 = Warning issued because an attempt has been made to open an invisible document with a linked design table that was modified externally, and the design table cannot be updated because the document cannot be displayed; you must make the document visible to open it and update the design table.
or 0x20000 = Warning appears because the design table is missing.
or 0x100000 = Warning appears if one or more references are missing when loading a file.
or 0x2000 = Warning appears because some sheets contain drawing views that are out of date with their external models.
or 0x20 = Warning appears because the document needs to be rebuilt.
or 0x2 = Warning appears because the document is read only.

or 0x1000 = Warning appears because some of the tolerances of the revolved feature dimensions were created in SOLIDWORKS 99 or earlier and are not synchronized with their corresponding dimensions in the sketch.
or 0x4 = Warning appears if the document is being used by another user.
or 0x10 = Warning appears because SOLIDWORKS now applies the scale of the sheet to the sketch entities on the sheet; which means that the sheet looks the same but dimension values are scaled.
or 0x400 = Warning appears because a configuration that a drawing view is referencing no longer exists in the model (part or assembly); the active configuration is used.
or 0x200 = Warning appears because the document is view only and a configuration other than the default configuration is set.
